Hey everyone,<p>I&#x27;ve been in tech world for 10+ years, most of them mobile. I am based in Asia, but for the last 3 years been working remotely. Clients mostly from USA, Europe, thus I have no problem with the time-zone. Charging 85usd&#x2F;h as of now.<p>I do specialise in building e2e products in Flutter (mobile framework). With it I can get a new contract pretty easily (due to my extensive portfolio and references). However, I&#x27;m thinking to make a move and check more of blockchain&#x2F;crypto development space. Am open for pretty much anything - as long as it involves blockchain and I can learn from people&#x2F;resource around me.<p>I seem to find quite some troubles finding leads for such jobs. Maybe am looking into some wrong places?<p>Tried:
- LinkedIn
- UpWork
- https:&#x2F;&#x2F;crypto.jobs&#x2F;
- https:&#x2F;&#x2F;cryptojobslist.com&#x2F;
